1. Binance will launch HYPEUSDT perpetual contract with a leverage of 75 times;
2. Whales continue to transfer about $6.47 million of PEPE to Binance, and have realized $5.5 million in profits on PEPE;
3. Abraxas Capital's mainstream tokens have made a floating profit of more than $13 million on short positions;
4. The giant whales cleared their long positions, turning from a profit of $27.88 million to a loss of $206,000 in 5 days;
5. Binance completed the WalletConnect Token (WCT) network integration;
6. The floating loss of the giant whale James Wynn's Bitcoin long orders expanded to $4 million, and the liquidation price was $104,610;
7. Analysis: Bitcoin may "healthily adjust" around $106,000, and institutions are bullish on the future market;
8. DCG poll shows that 77% of American respondents support decentralized AI;
9. Thailand SEC will block Bybit, 1000X, CoinEx, OKX and XT platforms in June;
10. Synthetix restores sUSD anchor to $1, and will increase the 420 pool collateral requirements;
11. Bithumb launches INIT and FLOCK Korean won markets;
12. James Wynn: I don’t regret opening large positions and high-multiple contracts, and will focus on building a community around moonpig;
13. Canary Staked CRO ETF submits S-1 form to apply for listing;
14. Buidlpad launches SAHARA community distribution, allocating $8.5 million in tokens;
15. James Wynn closed 40x leveraged BTC long positions, with a single loss of $37.42 million, and switched to 10x leveraged long PEPE.
